      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CEE CEE IN PARIS (6) has not raced since breaking in a Vicbred Super Series heat four months ago but showed ability earlier in her juvenile season, winning twice at this circuit and distance. Looks forward enough for the return after minor placings in two recent trials and finds a winnable assignment first up. PRINCE KENNY (1) made mistakes in two Brisbane starts at the maiden campaign but has been readied for this with a series of trials, finishing runner-up in his latest hitout at this circuit and distance. Gets the ace draw so expecting a bright start to the campaign. JET PLANE (2) has come from this barrier in both starts here since a spell and managed a fresh placing. Race fit now. PURPLE MOON (5) had been trialling well before blowing in the betting and finishing sixth on debut. Open to improvement.",
